OL,3,CFamilies affected by birth defect drug
OL,4,C'totally ignored' by government
OL,6,FEmma Murphy and Janet Williams have
OL,7,Fbeen campaigning for decades to get
OL,8,Fcompensation for families affected by
OL,9,Fthe epilepsy drug Sodium Valproate.
OL,11,FThey were prescribed the treatment
OL,12,Fwhen they were pregnant, which they
OL,13,Fsay caused severe disabilities in
OL,14,Ftheir children that "affect their
OL,15,Flives every single day."
OL,17,FThe Patient Safety Commissioner
OL,18,Frecommended the former Conservative
OL,19,Fgovernment set up interim payments and
OL,20,Fa full compensation scheme in February
OL,21,F2024.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
