OL,3,CFamilies affected by birth defect drug
OL,4,C'totally ignored' by government
OL,6,FBoth mothers, who have been fighting
OL,7,Ffor compensation for families affected
OL,8,Fby the drug for decades, say they live
OL,9,Fwith the daily worry of who will care
OL,10,Ffor their children when they die.
OL,12,FEmma said: "Compensation payments are
OL,13,Fso important because my husband and I
OL,14,Fwon't always be here but my son will
OL,15,Falways need our care. He will always
OL,16,Flive with us.
OL,18,F"Who will support him when I'm no
OL,19,Flonger here? Who will support our
OL,20,Fchildren when we're not here?"
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/11
